# Codemap Maintenance

## When to Refresh CODEMAP.md

After completing any of these structural changes, consider running `/codemap --refresh`:

- Created or deleted top-level directories
- Added a new entry point (new CLI script, API router, frontend page)
- Renamed or moved modules across directories
- Changed more than 10 files in a single feature
- Added or removed major dependencies
- Completed a significant architectural refactoring

## How to Refresh

```
/codemap --refresh
```

Or invoke the `codemap-updater` skill directly for more control.

## What Not to Refresh On

- Single-file edits within existing modules
- Documentation-only changes
- Test file additions that don't change architecture
- Config tweaks (`.env`, settings)
